 Jeffreys Bay - Just more than seven weeks into lockdown, Kouga Local Municipality Mayor, Horatio Hendricks, on Sunday gave an update on the number of Covid-19 cases in the region, following confirmation that an employee at Humansdorp FNB tested positive for the coronavirus on Friday. "While the patient resides in Humansdorp, she has family members in Jeffreys Bay who have also since been tested," he said. The number of positive cases in Kouga now stand at 11, with nine of these having recovered. The Mayor also commented on the partial opening of municipal offices; possible payment relief for residents and businesses affected by the coronavirus crisis; the resealing of roads and roll-out of wheelie bins; as well as local soup kitchens and food relief programmes. WATCH THE VIDEO:  Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 